@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="card shadow-lg border-0" style="background-color: #212529; border: 1px solid #343a40 !important;">
        <div class="card-header bg-dark border-bottom border-secondary py-3">
            <h2 class="text-white mb-0">
                <i class="bi bi-shield-check text-success me-2"></i>@ViewData["Title"]
            </h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card-body text-light p-4">
            <p class="text-secondary small italic">Last updated: February 16, 2026</p>
            
            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-info border-bottom border-secondary pb-2">1. Data Ownership</h4>
                <p>Your vehicle and session data are linked to your account via <strong>Identity Framework</strong>. We only temporarily store information necessary to calculate your parking fees and manage garage capacity.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-info border-bottom border-secondary pb-2">2. Geolocation Services</h4>
                <p>When using the "Find Parking" map, your browser's location is accessed locally via Leaflet.js. <strong>YourParkingSpot</strong> does not track your physical movements outside of the garage entry and exit points.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h4 class="text-info border-bottom border-secondary pb-2">3. Transparency</h4>
                <p>You can view your total revenue in the "Reports" section (for owners) or view your active sessions in real-time (for drivers).</p>
            </section>

            <div class="alert bg-dark border-info text-info mt-4">
                <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill me-2"></i>
                <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This application is a project for the ASP.NET Fundamentals course of SoftUni. Data is not shared with third parties.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card-footer bg-dark border-top border-secondary text-center py-3">
            <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm">
                Return Home
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>